'''Dimitri Mavrommatis''' is a Greek born asset manager and art collector based in [[Switzerland]] with additional residences in [[Paris]], [[London]] and [[New York City]].<ref name="adbusters">{{cite web|url=https://www.adbusters.org/magazine/100/1-percent-art.html|title=1% Art &#124; Adbusters|publisher=adbusters.org|accessdate=2015-09-20|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150908062703/https://www.adbusters.org/magazine/100/1-percent-art.html|archivedate=2015-09-08|df=}}</ref> He was on the European advisory board of [[Christie's]] and the international advisory board of [[Sotheby's]].<ref name="bloomberg">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=131455249&ticker=BID&previousCapId=99514488&previousTitle=Committee%20Encouraging%20Corporate%20Philanthropy|title=Dimitri Mavrommatis: Executive Profile & Biography - Businessweek|publisher=bloomberg.com|accessdate=2015-09-20}}</ref> In 2014 Sotheby's Geneva featured Mavrommatis' gems in their November jewelry sale in an event the auction house titled "The Passion of Collecting".<ref name="sothebys">{{cite web|url=http://www.sothebys.com/it/news-video/videos/2014/11/dimitri-mavrommatis-passion-collecting.html|title=Dimitri Mavrommatis: The Passion of Collecting &#124; Sotheby's|publisher=sothebys.com|accessdate=2015-09-20}}</ref> In 2012 [[ARTnews]] editor Milton Esterow listed Mavrommatis in the magazine's yearly top ten list of the worlds' 200 premiere art collectors.<ref name="artnews">{{cite web|url=http://www.artnews.com/2012/06/26/how-to-make-a-119-9-million-bid/|title=How to Make a $119.9 Million Bid &#124; ARTnews|publisher=artnews.com|accessdate=2015-09-20}}</ref> In addition to possessing a sizable collection of contemporary art including significant pieces by [[Pablo Picasso]], [[Joan Miro]], [[Alexander Calder]], [[Andy Warhol]] and [[Christopher Wool]], Mavrommatis owns one of the most important collections of [[Sèvres porcelain]] on the planet.<ref name="readperiodicals">{{cite web|url=http://www.readperiodicals.com/201303/2945639251.html|title=House of Wonders - A great collector of the finest works spanning the 18th to the 21st century, Dimitri Mavrommatis's... - Apollo|publisher=readperiodicals.com|accessdate=2015-09-20}}</ref>He also sold at Sotheby's one of the most important jewelry collections in the world with two new records for a sapphire and a ruby.
