A '''production set''' is the set of all combinations of inputs and outputs that comprise a [[technologically]] [[wikt:feasible|feasible]] way to produce.<ref>Intermediate Microeconomics, Hal R. Varian 1999,W. W. Norton & Company; 5th edition</ref> It is used as part of [[profit maximization]] calculations.

